"{\"uid\": \"iheart.com-content-2024-08-12-colin-jost-shares-injury-update-after-paris-olympics-exit\", \"text\": \"ByJason Hall  August 12, 2024  Saturday Night Livewriter andWeekend Updateco-anchorColin Jostshared an injury update after days after his gig as a correspondent for the2024 Paris Olympicsended prior to the event's conclusion.  \\\"Dude, are you OK?' That's the no. 1 text message I have received in the past 48 hours. Usually followed by, 'Heard your foot fell off,' Well, I am actually fine! And despite what big media conspiracies would have you believe, I wasn't 'sent home' from the Olympics.\\u00a0NBC simply looked at my food, declared me legally a leper, and exiled me here, to the island of Malta!\\\" Jost joked in a video shared on his Instagram account.  A post shared by Colin Jost (@colinjost)  \\\"Now Malta does not have many Olympians competing this year, but it does have thousands of 15-year-old British kids competing to see who can black out the fastest, and somehow they are all winning,\\\" he added. It also has this casino behind me, where I have blown the hundreds of dollars I have earned as a surfing correspondent.  \\\"But the real reason I am in Malta of course is because it was the site of 10 separate bubonic plague outbreaks. So they thought I would fit right in.\\\"  NBC confirmed that Jost, 42, the husband of actressScarlett Johansson, who was in Tahiti covering surfing events \\\"stayed longer than originally planned\\\" due to weather issues in a statement toUSA TODAYlast Thursday (August 8).  \\\"The competition ran long due to weather,\\\"NBCsaid. \\\"He had a great time, and everyone was thrilled with his coverage from Tahiti.\\\"  Jost previously shared posts on his Instagram account of a foot injury he suffered on a coral reef during his Tahiti coverage, which soon became a staph infection.  A post shared by Colin Jost (@colinjost)  \\\"I have been visiting the medical tent regularly. It's a weird feeling when you are in the medical tent way more than any of the athletes,\\\" Jost later toldNBC Sports.  \\\"The medical staff at this point, they know my name, they are very familiar with my badge ID number, they know I am allergic to penicillin,\\\" he added. \\\"They started saying, 'We need to see you every day.' At first, I was like, 'Oh, my God, guys, I like you, too.' And they were like, 'No, it's because the infection has not improved.\\\"  A post shared by Colin Jost (@colinjost)  \\\"I vow, I will not leave here unless it's being evacuated in a helicopter,\\\" Jost joked.  Australian weathermanLuke Bradnamtook over surfing coverage in Jost's absence,Reutersreported at the time.  \\u00a9 2025 iHeartMedia, Inc.\"}"